		{
			title: "Workin' with tHe pOt!"
			x: -5.5d
			y: 7.0d
			shape: "square"
			subtitle: "A Crucible can, when given heat and water, be used to combine certain items, to obtain new ones. Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"First off, the Crucible you're about to use, is NOT the Crucible from the Eidolon mod and this one has a different functionality. Let's see how you can use this thing."
				""
				"In order to make recipes in this Crucible, you'll have to fill it with water and provide a heat source underneath it. There are only two heat sources available and they're quite important for the recipes you're about to create."
				""
				"You can either use a regular Campfire, or a Soul Campfire. Some recipes will require the regular Campfire, and some of them, will require the Soul Campire. If the propper heat source is not provided, the items present in the Crucible's inventory, will be deleted. "
				""
				"Now, how do you actually craft something? It's quite simple. Place a bucket of Water in the Crucible, throw in the ingredients, and finally, throw in the Catalyst which will finalize the recipe. If the ingredients present in the Crucible will result in a valid recipe, the overlay shown on the screen, will show you the output and the Catalyst required to finish the recipe."
				""
				"\"What if I throw in the Crucible a wrong item?\""
				""
				"We'd suggest being careful with the Crucible. One wrong item in its inventory and all of your items will be gone, since you can't get items out. Same thing will happen if you throw in, the wrong Catalyst."
				""
				"\"Ok, how do I reset the Crucible if I mess it up?\""
				""
				"Just place a new bucket of water in the Crucible."
				""
				"Finally, use JEI to see what recipes you have access to, and which ones will require a Soul Campfire."
			]
			dependencies: [
				"3BC1CFB22EDA4D74"
				"20565A3484CED967"
			]
			id: "2045087C068870F6"
			tasks: [{
				id: "19B637F8DBADC266"
				type: "item"
				item: "decursiomod:crucible"
			}]
			rewards: [{
				id: "24A17BA3B61424DF"
				type: "item"
				item: "minecraft:campfire"
			}]
		}
		{
			x: -2.5d
			y: 7.0d
			shape: "square"
			subtitle: "Used to execute rituals. Left Click to view setup example"
			description: [
				"{image:kubejs:textures/eidolon/example4.png width:170 height:100 align:1}"
				""
				"The ritual in the example above, is the Ritual of Moonlight. It will make it night time. This ritual will require 4 stone hands. To start any ritual, just right-click the brazier with a Flint and Steel."
				""
				"Note that quite a numerous number of items are obtained through a Ritual. While Eidolon has JEI support, it is not very well implemented, so you can't just press \"R\" on an item to see its recipe, you'll have to press \"U\" on one of the ingredients instead. We'll try to assist you with this issue through the descriptions of our quests."
				""
				"Lastly, note that all the Brazier Ritual recipes will require the Stone Hands to be on the same Y level as the Brazier itself. Same goes to the advanced items holders, such as the Necrotic Focus. DO NOT ignore this."
			]
			dependencies: ["3BC1CFB22EDA4D74"]
			id: "077199D0B5C0CEDD"
